How the mattress and the somier are chosen: women and men are looking for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really confers its quality on a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, mattress and somier.
First of all, they must be complementary to perfection in order to adapt to specific users.
During the election many elements come into play, including the owner's weight, height, state of health and sex.
Also important is the type of interior in which the mattress and the somier are placed.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they often weigh considerably more than usual polyurethane mattresses.
It is therefore necessary to turn them more frequently.
If the central canals are not properly aired and above them are on a firm basis, they keep inside the moisture. Even wet can appear below.
When choosing a bed, customs are also influenced.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have problems feeling well on a lower and tougher surface.
"Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep as well here."
"For his sharp shoulders, heels and hips needed mattresses with a soft viscoelastic layer."
"This type of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who have problems with the nervous system, so they receive bad information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in the stuffed furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have spent time preferring viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italian Magniflex, but also the Czech Tropic mark."
You don't have to be a NHL player anymore to be able to appreciate viscoelastics.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes your rigidity and forms depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it won't turn around like after a hard game.
Just sleep better.
Viscoelastics also works as protection against lakes.
By choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of its feet, i.e. between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of individual rooms, for example singles, it is recommended at least 120 to 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, a simple rule can be applied to calculate the width: when you lay your face up, you should have your hands comfortably curly towards your elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, expert from Cechu čalouník to dekorater, who has been dealing with the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomic furniture, which she teaches in specialized schools for many years.
In the double rooms, each one needs his own somier and mattress, so during the purchase you need to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to assemble the dreamers at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
The foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, the models with spring interiors a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"When you touch it with your hand or when you sit on the mattress, you should certainly not notice the docks," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a specified somier type.
The fully-accompanied bedrooms, where the mattress and the base are like sesames, have no meaning in the bedroom.
The mattresses breathe badly and you can't wash your bottom, which is often done today.
And, given that every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will start to remind us of a large (and congested) tamiz.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that speak of a life of mattress up to 25 years or even a life assurance.
However, everything has one but.
For this reason, sellers give advice: in mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully handle cleaning and washing of the bottom, but better add a mattress protector that can be removed and washed easily.
Although mattresses are currently made with zipper closure throughout their perimeter, so when opening them they remain in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their handling in the larger models (and for one person) when raising the mattress may seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In the bed, instead of a somier, do you have a firm table?
Never!
So much for the beds designed to spend one night the visits.
However, it must do (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes on the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the docks in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulated sheet sumers containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses can be used (for example, a combination of latex and coconut fiber), although it is always better a somier with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar area are reinforced and its rigidity can be regulated.
Articulated sheet sumers should not be used with a spring mattress, since they do not react to reclination.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the blades, shoulder protection can also be used.
This is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets so that they "round" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men with very broad shoulders, this is something very important.
They are even remembered by the mattress manufacturers who, in the "male" areas, began to use a softer area precisely around their shoulders.
They also remember women, for which they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are puzzles with cross-structure or boards with the so-called multitorsion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the tension is lowered.
It should also be noted that although you use the appropriate mattress and somier, if you use a bad pillow (large and "wet"), most benefits will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: pillows must hold the head and corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of the shoulders can relax.
The appropriate size recommended is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
On the lower side, the pillow must be at the same level (when combined with the somier with shoulder reinforcement or softer area of the mattress) than the height of the shoulders.
The modern mattresses have something to do with the original straw-filled mattresses.
Manufacturers continue to use, more and more often, natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are fashionable.
Petroleum raw materials, with which the polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils such as castor or soy.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vašíček of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used during the manufacture of the mattress base, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also choose the microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma to the forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "refresh" with vegetable extracts of breeze, so that the mattress bottom absorbs the heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the bottom.
The red pepper extract improves the circulation of blood, so that women feel more warm.
The currently favorite?
The mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with a structure of adapted cells, making them more permeable than those of normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various cold and viscoelastic foam rigidities allows you to manufacture mattresses from various areas that know perfectly where your head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who perform a therapeutic function often have lower VAT, since they are considered to be health-care.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It's complicated to save on mattresses and dreams.
Sometimes the offers of manufacturers or sellers can be approved, which sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a memory foam memory attached to the base for 11,990 crowns.
The second one is obtained free of charge.
The era of viscoelastics with an open cell structure and a great density began with Tempur's "cosmic" material.
Initially it emerged as material for NASA, because during the take-off astronaut loas they were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempor softens with the heat and hardens with the cold.
Therefore, the warm human body has a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent lakes from occurring, although also to improve comfort during sleep.
The viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
National manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and similar.
More and more parents use tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children keeps more and more people thinking about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, to the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Anička Janatková.
For the moment the device has the approximate size of a box of eyeglasses, but will soon be reduced to the size of a clock.
Many people were afraid of the missing Anička case and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We're all trying to tell ourselves that it's not about spying, but about another way to reduce the possibility of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are placed in someone's pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases."
"Most customers actually buy it for security reasons," adds Pilin.
In your opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in case of an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns about the fact that if the child does not want to carry it, he will simply throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity when they intentionally lose certain things if they want to avoid being controlled."
"Before that, parents had enormous trust in mobile phones, but they could be turned off as easily as the tracking device," says Bočková.
In his view, it is questionable whether such a device is really useful in the event of an attack.
"If this is a prepared kidnapping, the author will almost always check whether the child has any kind of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices is being extended, it will also look for them, since their sale will no doubt be made with much publicity."
"In such cases, offenders always go one step ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
However, add that such devices can help in the event of an improvised attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the company RC Monitoring, which provides follow-up services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to regularly send the position after a certain period."
"If damaged, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person concerned."
"The most expensive devices incorporate a tilt meter, so if the person simply slips and stays motionless, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," says Čech.
