EU changes rules to obtain visas
Persons should attend Visa Applicant Service Centres before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and as well as the waiting time.
As of 10 January 2011, it will change the procedure of processing a visa at the United States Embassy and consulates.
With the new procedure, most applicants should go to Visa Applicant Service Centres (ASC) prior to their interview in the Consular Section.
ASC staff shall take biometric information from the applicant, which shall be reviewed by the Consular Section prior to the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for applicants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer required to make a payment to conclude the appointment, another payment to process the visa application and another for the courier service to deliver the document.
The applicant will only make a single payment covering the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa cases on request (including temporary workers visas) and $390 for visas by traders and investors.
Those who wish to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Officer, but will only go to the nearest AUC where they will submit their documents and take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken in the AUC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain in this less time than in the past.
Similarly, those applying for visas at the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of 26 dollars.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
